      testing packages

%br

.section-grouping

  %h2(id="devrhel61")
    Install the Red Hat Enterprise Linux/CentOS 6.2 x86_64 testing packages

  %h3
    1. If the system is using RHN Classic, enable the RHEL 6.2 Optional
    Channel

  %p.note
    This step isn't needed if you're using RHN Subscription Management.

  %p
    %pre
      $ sudo rhn-channel --add --channel=rhel-x86_64-server-optional-6

  %h3 2. Add the Aeolus RHEL/CentOS 6.2 Testing yum repository

  %p
    %pre
      :preserve
        $ sudo curl -o /etc/yum.repos.d/rhel-aeolus-testing.repo \
        &nbsp; http://repos.fedorapeople.org/repos/aeolus/conductor/testing/rhel-aeolus-testing.repo

  %h3 3. Install the Aeolus packages

  %p
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    If you are using RHN Classic, use this command to install Aeolus:

  %p
    %pre
      $ sudo yum install aeolus-all

  %p
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    If you are using RHN Subscription Management (instead of RHN Classic), use
    this command to install Aeolus:

  %p
    %pre
      $ sudo yum install aeolus-all --enablerepo=rhel-6-server-optional-rpms

  %p
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This will install the latest Aeolus testing
    packages, along with their dependencies, on the RHEL/CentOS 6.2 x86_64
    system.

